L-3 Communications Security and Detection Systems, Inc. Key Developments

L-3 Communications Security & Detection Systems Inc. Wins $4,110,009 Federal Contract
Mar 17 17
L-3 Communications Security & Detection Systems Inc. won a $4,110,009 federal contract from the U.S. Department of Homeland Security's Transportation Security Administration for alarm, signal and security detection equipment for the Charleston International Airport, South Carolina.


L-3 Communications Security & Detection Systems Inc Wins $3.89 Million Federal Contract
Mar 10 17
L-3 Communications Security & Detection Systems Inc. won a $3,885,009 federal contract from the U.S. Department of Homeland Security's Transportation Security Administration for alarm, signal and security detection equipment.


Vivid Technologies Appoints Freddie Achom as Non-Executive Chairman
Sep 23 16
Vivid Technologies has named Freddie Achom as its new Non-Executive Chairman. As part of the company's plans to expand into the Middle East telecoms sector and other developing markets. Achom has been brought on to advise Founder Omer Khan and the Vivid board. The appointment follows a recent joint venture exclusive agency distribution agreement between the company and Kuwait-based Media Phone Plus that will serve the Kuwait, Bahrain and Iraq region of the Middle East. Freddie Achom comes with a wealth of experience within the venture investment and financial services sector. He is the CEO and Founder of Rosemont Group Capital Partners who last year invested in the company alongside Sunbridge Ventures, Telefonica and Conrad Labs.


